<plot>Students from the famed Heifetz violin class at USC perform masterworks including movements from the Brahms, Tchaikovsky, and Khachaturian concertos, Franck sonata and Bach unaccompanied sonatas/partitas, Bach double concerto, plus movements from Beethoven string quartets....all under the guidance of one Jascha Heifetz. Brooks Smith serves as piano accompanist. Also included is a parody done by Heifetz, an imitation of a horrible violinist who had auditioned for the class.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?274150</url></doc>
